The paper proposes a model for sequential recommendation using both long-term preferences and recent purchase/rating patterns. This involves machine learning techniques and data analysis, which are typically associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with sequential data, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed model on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
